cs.CY, cs.SI, cs.CE, cs.DC, cs.SE 

This paper discusses the development of a framework for cyber-physical systems to deliver a data-driven Circular Economy model in a city context. This involves the integration of various technologies and systems to create a smart city that is sustainable and efficient. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CY (Computers and Society) as it deals with the intersection of technology and society. Other likely categories include cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as the framework involves crowdsourcing and real-time decision making, cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) as the framework aims to create a circular economy model, cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) as the framework involves the integration of various systems, and cs.SE (Software Engineering) as the framework involves the development of software systems.
